label.value: proximal-most point of head of femur

value.value: The proximal-most point of the head of a femur.

label.value: proximal-most point of head of humerus

value.value: The proximal-most point of the head of a humerus.

label.value: proximal-most point of ventral tubercle of humerus

value.value: The proximal-most point of the ventral tubercle of a humerus.

label.value: proximal-most point of greater trochanter of femur

value.value: The proximal-most point of the greater trochanter of a femur.
The molar tooth of the lower jaw that is phylogenetically number 4.
The premolar tooth of the lower jaw that is phylogenetically number 4.
The premolar tooth of the lower jaw that is phylogenetically number 3.
The molar tooth of the upper or lower jaw that is phylogenetically number 4.
The premolar tooth of the upper or lower jaw that is phylogenetically number 3.
The molar tooth of the upper jaw that is phylogenetically number 4.
The premolar tooth of the upper jaw that is phylogenetically number 4.
The premolar tooth of the upper jaw that is phylogenetically number 3.
The ridge of the trochlea on a humerus lies in the middle of the distal end of a humerus on the lateral side of the trochlea and the medial side of the capitulum (capitellum).
The tibial tuberosity is on the anterior side of a tibia and is where a patella ligament attaches.
The articular surface of a talus that interacts with a tibia. It has a deep depression that forms the trochlear groove and is bounded by the medial and lateral condyles.
The furrow between the lateral and medial condyles of the trochlea of talus.
An articular prominence of a talus that engages with the tibia.
The medial condyle of talus is an articular prominence of bone on medial side of the trochlea of a talus, which engages with the tibia.
The lateral condyle of talus is an articular prominence of bone on the lateral side of the trochlea of a talus, which engages with the tibia.

label.value: ridge of medial condyle of talus

value.value: The crest of the medial condyle of a talus.

label.value: ridge of lateral condyle of talus

value.value: The crest of the lateral condyle of a talus.
A depression that runs between the two facets of a talus that interact with a calcaneum.

An anatomical structure that protrudes from the head region. In vertebrates, this includes the part of the cranium (skull) in front of the zygomatic arches that also holds the teeth, palat, and nasal cavity. In invertebrates it is the forward extension of the carapace and/or the piercing mouthparts.
Nasal bone on the left side of an organism when in anatomical position.
Nasal bone on the right side of an organism when in anatomical position.
Zygomatic arch on the left side of an organism when in anatomical position.
Zygomatic arch on the right side of an organism when in anatomical position.
A condyle on the distal end and lateral side of a radius.
A condyle on the distal end and medial side of a radius that interacts with the ulna.
The articular surface on the distal end of a radius that interacts with carpals.

label.value: articular surface for the tibia on the talus

value.value: Contact surface between the tibia and the talus located on the talus.
A foramen of the skull found at either posterior angle of the hard palate, for the transmission of the descending palatine vessels and greater palatine nerve.

A foramen of the skull found at either posterior angle of the hard palate behind the greater palatine foramen. One or more lesser palatine foramina perforate the pyramidal process of the palatine bone and carry the lesser palatine nerve.
A pulp-dentin complex or endodont that is part of a calcareous tooth.

label.value: posterior articular facet for talus of calcaneus

value.value: Posterior-most facet on the proximal surface of the calcaneus for the articulation of the talus bone.

label.value: middle articular facet for talus of calcaneus

value.value: Middle facet on the proximal surface of the calcaneus for the articulation of the talus bone.

label.value: anterior articular facet for talus of calcaneus

value.value: Anterior-most facet on the proximal surface of the calcaneus for the articulation of the talus bone.
The calcaneus body is the part of the bone not used for articulation with other bones.
A raised projection on the calcaneus.
A raised projection on the lateral side of a calcaneus.
A raised projection on the medial side of a calcaneus.
The antorbital notch is a prominence of bone located anterolaterally of the antorbital fenestra.

Part of the orbital plate formed by the jugal (part of the zygomatic), lacrimal (which is sometimes fused), sometimes nasal (typically in species with elongated rostra), and maxilla bones anterior to the orbit.
A hollow (fossa) in the preorbital region, typically lying on the maxillary bone, although sometimes can touch nasal bones (e.g., modern Equus).
At the dorsal part of the base of the calcaneal tuberoisty is a pointed process called the coracoid process.
A craniometric point at the junction of the posterior midline border of the vomer with the sphenoid bone on the sphenovomerine suture.
A suture joining a sphenoid bone with the alae of a vomer to form a schindylesis type of joint.
Any of the post-canine teeth, which are the multicuspidate molars or premolars used for shearing and grinding food in mammals.
An anatomical point on the antero-ventral margin of foramen magnum in the median plane.
A craniometric point on the ventral surface of the intersphenoid suture, along the midline of the skull.
